The paper discusses a new listening comprehension task that involves spoken content, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of speech recognition errors on machine comprehension, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes approaches to mitigate the impact of speech recognition errors, which involves optimization and modeling techniques, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Learning) also possible sub-categories.
